FT  22 FEB 92 / Finance &amp; The Family: Financial Times A-Z of Personal
Finance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Too often, ordinary investors are offered financial products they do not
understand, by people whose motives they understandably suspect. The
FINANCIAL TIMES A-Z of PERSONAL FINANCE, published with next Friday's paper
and repeated with Saturday's, cuts an alphabetic swathe through the money
jungle, from Annuities to Zero-dividend securities, stripping away the
jargon to offer a down-to-earth guide to many types of product.
