'The equity market is a bit problematic with the current wage negotiations.
The wage settlement in the steel industry was too high, but there is a
chance the banks will get a deal not above 6 per cent. That would be a
signal for the public sector and boost shares.'
Mr Ramm expects interest-
sensitive sectors, such as financials, construction and consumer
demand-related stocks, to react first, with engineering and exporters
advancing later.
