<HEADLINE>
FT  21 FEB 92 / Technology (Worth Watching): Sound around the houses
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A SOUND system which upstages today's two-speaker stereo sound by giving the
impression that music is coming from all around has long been promised. Now
Perfect Pitch of London has developed a system called Om which, it believes,
will bring such an effect within the price range of smaller recording
studios.
The home stereo user will not need to buy extra equipment. Instead, a devise
in the studio, incorporated at the mixing stage, filters the sound by
reflecting it off an electronic circuit.
This fools the ear of the listener, when playing the music at home, into
thinking that the sound is emerging from in front, behind and from each side
 -rather than from the two speakers.
The Perfect Pitch equipment to achieve these psycho-acoustic effects is
available from Select Systems of Hanworth, Middlesex, for Pounds 3,500.
Select Systems: UK, 081 893 8662.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
