<PROFILE>_AN-CBUBBAGHFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>920221
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  21 FEB 92 / Technology (Worth Watching): Smart card takes charge of
meter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
EVEN THE traditional British gas meter looks set to be replaced by a
high-tech alternative.
British Gas, together with Landis &amp; Gyr Energy Management, of Telford, has
developed a smart card system, called Quantum, which is now on trial and
looks set to replace the coin meter.
To use the system the gas consumer takes a gas card to a newsagent or
convenience store where the shopkeeper credits gas on to the card through a
counter-top charging unit - a minimum of Pounds 1 or a maximum of Pounds 9
can be put on the card. Information from the newsagent is collected by the
British Gas regional accounting centre over the phone network on a daily
basis.
By inserting the card in the 'slot', the user can see the amount of gas
credited on a liquid crystal display incorporated into the unit. As gas is
used, the amount credited drops.
British Gas: UK, 091 216 3807.
