<TEXT>
AN advisory panel to the US Food and Drug Administration (FDA) yesterday
recommended that silicone gel breast implants not be available to the
general public.
The panel recommended that the implants be limited to a tightly controlled
group of women for breast enlargement who would be studied for possible
adverse health effects.
