<HEADLINE>
FT  21 FEB 92 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PRESIDENT FW de Klerk's announcement an hour before close of trade that he
planned to hold a referendum on his reform programme shook Johannesburg. The
overall index, which had been 30 points higher before the news, closed up 3
at 3,541, while the industrial index shed a 35-point gain to close 3 down at
4,325. The all-gold index gained 5 to 1,237.
</TEXT>
