<TEXT>
IN ITS first year as a public company Headline Book Publishing saw pre-tax
profit double to Pounds 1.3m.
The result compared with Pounds 637,000 for 1990, and was boosted by a swing
from net interest payable to net interest receivable after the flotation
last April. At December 31 cash stood at Pounds 1.3m.
Earnings per share rose to 9p (6.9p) and the final dividend is 2.5p for a
