mooted in January, gained 2p to 36p. The A shares added 32p to 163p.
Polyfinance, which has operations in France and Germany, said it wanted to
expand its laundry business into the UK and identify cost savings.
Polymark has accepted the offer. Directors hold 0.23 per cent of the
ordinary and 8.44 per cent of the A shares.
The offers will be made by Societe Generale Merchant Bank on behalf of
Polyfinance.
