<TEXT>
RECESSION and a series of high-profile trade disputes with the US have
heightened the Canadian public's unease over the creation of a North
American free-trade area (Nafta), Bernard Simon writes from Toronto.
However, Prime Minister Brian Mulroney has so far shown no sign of bowing to
